The strings, frets, and bridge are all components of a guitar. The strings are the metal wires that vibrate when you pluck them. The frets are the thin metal strips that divide the strings into different positions for playing notes. The bridge is the part of the guitar that holds the strings in place and helps to amplify the sound.

